description._value: Here, metabolome analysis using LC-QTOF-MS was conducted to figure out the metabolome alternations in Arabidopsis overaccumulating and lacking flavonoids.
Harvested plant samples were immediately frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at minus 80 degree Celsius until use.

Frozen or freeze-dried samples were extracted with 5 ul or 50 ul of 80% MeOH containing 2.5 uM lidocaine per mg fresh or dry weight, respectively, which was an internal standard for the positive mode analysis, using a mixer mill (MM300, Retsch) together with a zirconia bead per tube for 10 min at 20 Hz. After centrifugation for 10 min and filtration with an HLB uElution plate (Waters), the extracts (1 ul) were analyzed using LC-QTOF-MS.

Waters Acquity UPLC system
column, Acquity bridged ethyl hybrid (BEH) C18 (1.7 um, 2.1 mm * 100 mm, Waters)
solvent system, solvent A (water including 0.1% formic acid) and solvent B (acetonitrile including 0.1% formic acid); gradient program, 99.5% A/0.5% B at 0 min, 99.5% A/0.5% B at 0.1 min, 20% A/80% B at 10 min, 0.5% A/99.5% B at 10.1 min, 0.5% A/99.5% B at 12.0 min, 99.5% A/0.5% B at 12.1 min and 99.5% A/0.5% B at 15.0 min
flow rate, 0.3 ml/min
column temperature, 40 degree Celsius.

Waters Xevo G2 Q-Tof
capillary voltage, +3.0 keV
cone voltage, 25.0 V
source temperature, 120 degree Celsius
desolvation temperature, 450 degree Celsius
cone gas flow, 50 l/h
desolvation gas flow, 800 l/h
collision energy, 6 V
mass range, m/z 100 - 1500
scan duration, 0.1 s
interscan delay, 0.014 s
mode, centroid
polarity, positive
lockspray, leucine enkephalin
scan duration, 1.0 s
interscan delay, 0.1 s
Alignment, MassLynx version 4.1 (Waters).

After alignment, deisotope and cutoff of the low-intensity peaks (<500 counts) and the intensity values of the remaining peaks were divided by those of the lidocaine ([M + H]+, m/z 235.1804) for normalization. The processed data were used for the PCA with SIMCA-P 11.5. The log2-transformed value was used for the HCA with MeV 4.8 (http://mev.tm4.org/).

title._value: Metabolome profiling using LC-MS in Arabidopsis overaccumulating and lacking flavonoids
